frameDefinitions: A Protagonist comes to suffer from a Disease, often implicitly acquired from a Source.
A Protagonist is sensitive to a Trigger, which has the potential to cause some kind of reaction in the Protagonist.  '' 'Mr. Clinton and his wife Hillary are allergic to cats.'
An Agent matches location with an Entity in order to fulfill some  Purpose.

This frame concerns an Addict's physiological or psychological compulsive dependence on an Addictant, the substance or behavior to which the Addict is addicted. '' 'Although she was never a big fan of drugs, she became hooked on that designer drug instantly.'
An Entity undergoes some change (the Event) that is (or is construed as) punctual.
frameExamples: Mr. Clinton and his wife Hillary are <t>allergic</t> to cats.
I ca n't remember how many times he <t>visited</t> ! DNI
Although she was never a big fan of drugs, she became <t>hooked</t> on that designer drug instantly.
This <t>happens</t> to me all the time.
listRoleDefinitions: The time at which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> contracts the <fen>Disease</fen>.

The location at which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> contracts the <fen>Disease</fen>.  It is different from the <fen>Source</fen> (usually marked with 'from') in that it does not necessarily mean that it was contact with the <fen>Place</fen> that actually led to infection.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> occurs as the External Argument of the targets in this frame. The <fen>Protagonist</fen> represents the one exhibiting the response to the <fen>Trigger</fen>.

The <fen>Trigger</fen> most commonly occurs in a PP Complement headed by <ment>to</ment>. The <fen>Trigger</fen> is that substance or element which causes a health response in the <fen>Protagonist</fen>.
The sentient entity that is temporarily with the <fen>Entity</fen> in order to fulfil some <fen>Purpose</fen>.

The physical entity that is permanently associated with entities or characteristics that the <fen>Agent</fen> wishes to use for some <fen>Purpose</fen>.  During the visit, the <fen>Agent</fen> matches location with the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time at which a visit is made.
A description of the position of the <fen>Agent</fen> during the visit.
The <fen>Addict</fen> is physiologically or psychologically dependent on a substance or a behavior.
<fen>Addictant</fen> is the substance or behavior to which the <fen>Addict</fen> is dependent.
This role identifies the entity, concrete or abstract.
This role identifies the time when the event occurs.
This role identifies where the event takes place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>Pat's</fex> allergy to dairy products is severe.
Some people are very sensitive <fex>to chemicals in the environment</fex>.
